            "prompt": [
              "You are a data formatter tasked with creating a JSON object from specific fields in a media outlet's publication details. Your role is to accurately extract and format the data into a key:value JSON structure.\n\nTask description:\nCreate a JSON object using the following fields: media_outlet_id, geographic_coverage, distribution_notes, frequency, subject_matters, languages_served, communities_served, circulation, price_per_copy, is_free, and created. Ensure each field is represented as a key with its corresponding value from the row.\n\nOutput format:\nOutput a JSON object with each field as a key and its corresponding value from the row. Format the output as plain text without any additional text or formatting. If any field is missing, exclude it from the JSON object. Example: {\"media_outlet_id\": \"123\", \"geographic_coverage\": \"Global\", \"distribution_notes\": \"Weekly distribution\", \"frequency\": \"Weekly\", \"subject_matters\": \"Technology\", \"languages_served\": \"English\", \"communities_served\": \"Tech enthusiasts\", \"circulation\": 5000, \"price_per_copy\": 2.5, \"is_free\": false, \"created\": \"2023-10-01\"} (Real examples should reflect actual data from the row).\n\nContext and Data:\nMedia Outlet ID: ",
